<p>Launched from the offices of the occupied UBS offices at Sun Street, London, Occupation Records is run by an independent collective of occupiers, for occupiers, in support of Occupy London, Occupy Britain, and the Occupy movement worldwide.</p>

<p>The label offers live recordings from the occupations as part of the Occupy Live! series, benefit albums, and releases albums by artists within the Occupy movement. In the spirit of the movement, all releases are offered on a pay-what-you-can basis, and are DMR free.</p>

<p>All profit benefits the Occupy movement. The breakdown is 25% to the Occupy London general fund, 25% available specifically to other occupations across Britain and Ireland, and 50% to a fighting fund for the Occupy movement worldwide.</p>

<p>The collective behind Occupation Records include music industry professionals, students, and revolutionaries. The label is the first to come out of the movement. All power to the 99%</p>
